                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d796">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 M Nielsen, Niels/61: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-09-14T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 14, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>316. Reference Mukden’s mail despatch August 4,<note n="41" xml:id="d796fn41">Not
                        printed.</note> concerning Nielsen. Inquire of Mukden what is present status
                    of case, and telegraph Department, adding comment from Myers and yourself which
                    would assist the Department in deciding whether or not to instruct Tokyo to make
                    further representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
